# Customer app, auth, and AI

Read **CLAUDE.md** app flows, **agents.md** auth and AI sections, and **workspace-packages.mdc**.

## Customer app

- Slug-based multi-tenant entry from App.tsx URL routing (`hooks/useRestaurantSlugRoute.tsx`)
- Reel UX: vertical scroll via `@minute-menus/reels` (`ReelCard`), watch sessions, cart, checkout
- Hard cap on dishes shown in reel — product requirement
- Separate customer auth (sign-up, OTP, profile) from owner Supabase session — methods in supabase-service
- Price display: `@minute-menus/currency`
- Auth button loading: `@minute-menus/ui` (`ButtonSpinner`)

## Owner login

Google OAuth and email/password via Supabase; redirect URL uses VITE_SITE_URL in production. Login loading uses `@minute-menus/ui`.

## AI

`@minute-menus/ai` — Anthropic Claude. Pinned model for cost/speed. `services/geminiService.ts` is a re-export shim only. Missing API key or API failure → friendly fallback string, never uncaught throw to UI.

**Secrets:** Never inject `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` / `GEMINI_API_KEY` / Replicate tokens into the Vite client (`define`, `VITE_*`). No `dangerouslyAllowBrowser`. Platform keys stay on Vercel `api/**` only. Owner keys are saved via Supabase/`owner_settings` and used server-side; UI exposes `hasAnthropicApiKey` only. See **`ai-api-key-security.mdc`**.

## Types

Shared interfaces in `@minute-menus/types` — extend there before inline types in pages. Do not recreate a root `types.ts` shim.
